Vicinity of Ranomafana National Park, large (150 ha) sandy flat wetland called Ampasina and surrounding forest; Ampasina is 3-4 hours walk E of Amboditanimena which is on national road 25 between Vohiparara and Ambalakindresy. Ampasina also easily reached from Ambalakindresy. Vegetation in Ampasina mostly short grasses and sedges 30-60 cm tall, with at least 5 species of Utricularia, a Drosera sp., an Aloe sp., and many terrestrial orchids. Streams with Weinmannia commersonii along edges. The forest is dominated by Dypsis decipiens and is of short stature (6-10 m) with abundant Weinmannia spp., Syzygium spp., Araliaceae, and Sapindaceae.
